#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Pāsādakampanavagga "
msgstr "2. Shaking the Stilt Longhouse "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Mahapphalasutta "
msgstr "12. Very Fruitful "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.267, sc1
msgctxt "sn51.12:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when the four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they’re very fruitful and beneficial. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā? "
msgstr "How so? "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.4"
msgid "iti me chando na ca atilīno bhavissati, na ca atippaggahito bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhitto bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhitto bhavissati. "
msgstr "They think: ‘My enthusiasm won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.5"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And they meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.6"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.7"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.8"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:1.9"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn51.12:2.1"
msgid "Vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy … "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.2"
msgid "cittasamādhi … "
msgstr "mental development … "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.3"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.4"
msgid "iti me vīmaṃsā na ca atilīnā bhavissati, na ca atippaggahitā bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhittā bhavissati. "
msgstr "They think: ‘My inquiry won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.5"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And they meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.6"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.7"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.8"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.9"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

msgctxt "sn51.12:2.10"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way they’re very fruitful and beneficial. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn51.12:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitesu kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu catūsu iddhipādesu evaṃ bahulīkatesu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti … pe …. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way, a mendicant wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and becoming one again … controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.268, sc4
msgctxt "sn51.12:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitesu kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu catūsu iddhipādesu evaṃ bahulīkatesu, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way, they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.12:4.2"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

